rComments: Jon Johnson is very, very kind prof. He's very approachable and understanding of circumstances that might be affecting students. However, in comparison to other classes worth 0.5, the workload regarding essays and the readings were a bit much and overall I felt the course was somewhat time-crunched.

rComments: First year seminar about Indigenous history of Toronto. Informing course content. A lot of reflections and two bigger assignments, but no exams or tests. Jon is a really nice prof but his grading on papers is kind of tough. Sometimes the lectures were a bit dry. Overall pretty chill class if you prefer writings to tests.
